9 Section 1. Section 90-5-101, MCA, is amended to read:
10 "90-5-101. Definitions. As used in this part, unless the context otherwise requires, the following
11 definitions apply:
12 (1) "Agricultural enterprises" includes but is not limited to producing, warehousing, storing,
13 fattening, treating, handling, distributing, or selling farm products or livestock.
14 (2) "Bonds" means bonds, refunding bonds, notes, or other obligations issued by a municipality or
15 county under the authority of this part, including without limitation short-term bonds or notes issued in
16 anticipation of the issuance of long-term bonds or notes.
17 (3) "Electric energy generation facility" means any combination of a physically connected
18 generator or generators, associated prime movers, and other associated property and transmission facilities
19 and upgrades and improvements of transmission facilities, including appurtenant land and improvements and
20 personal property, that are normally operated together to produce and transfer electric power. The term
21 includes but is not limited to generating facilities that produce and transfer electricity from coal-fired steam
22 turbines, oil or gas turbines, wind turbines, solar power sources, fuel cells, or turbine generators that are driven
23 by falling water.
24 (4) "Family services provider" means organizations, including nonprofit corporations, that provide
25 human services for children and adults, including but not limited to early care services for children, youth
26 services, health services, social services, habilitative services, rehabilitative services, preventive care, and
27 supportive services, and training, educational, and referral activities in support of human services.
28 (5) "Governing body" means the board or body in which the general legislative powers of the
